  "body": "Context:\r\n- web3 relies on a forked version of bignumber that doesn't use regex lookahead, and from my understanding regex lookahead isn't support when evaluating JS in Otto\r\n- There was a problem with the latest web3 \"release\" that required an additional build step for dist (adamb can elaborate on this)\r\n- status-react currently adds a new version of bignumber to solve a regression bug in certain JS environments that causes basic numeric operations to hang completely\r\n- This forked version that web3 relies on doesn't solve the abovementioned numeric bug AFAICT\r\n\r\nFuture steps and concerns:\r\n1. We ideally want to use the same version of `web3.js` and `bignumber.js` across the board for simplicity\r\n2. If the significant number bug can occur for smart contracts inside jail, we need to figure out how to deal with that - using another dependency like another version of bignumber is confusing for people who expect `fromWei` to just work\r\n3. We need to decide on if and how we should fork web3 and/or bignumber in order to incorporate these fixes (no lookahead and numeric bug), as well as how involved we should be with upstream (roma started working on nolookahead in some capacity I think?)\r\n\r\n**Conclusion from Slack chat with roman: we fork `web3` and `bignumber` that includes both relevant fixes.**\r\n\r\n- `bignumber.js` up to date repo under org with numeric fix\r\n- `web3` up to date repo under org with our `bignumber.js` dependency\r\n- update dependencies across board (x2-x3)\r\n- check envs: RN/webview/otto for regressions\r\n- basic process doc for keeping up to date with upstream (previously we had web3 fork that became outdated)\r\n- submit PR upstream",
